caption: Everything is good, just wish portions were bigger

At the first moment  you come to this restaurant  the personel give you an enjoyable feeling. Very friendly crew, it is a friendly restaurant to hang out with friends or with your date. very good  food, professional  chief cook and stuff, competitive  pay and generous  service. Warmly recommended.

Omg sooo Delish !!!! So I ordered the ribs, Mac & cheese, and collard greens. It was my first time hearing about this establishment, so I decided to try it. It was a great choice, the ribs were huge and well cooked, the greens were seasoned so well, and the Mac & cheese was awesome. Love this place, and this will be my go to for BBQ !!!

I don’t understand the negative reviews; Fletcher’s is amazing!!! My delivery came early and everything was awesome! The brisket is seasoned perfectly, cornbread is a generous size and delicious, and rib tips are so tasty. Get the banana pudding!!! YUM. I will definitely be back!

I ordered the “make your own” combo to be delivered by a specified time. It arrived almost an hour early and without one of the sides. I tried calling, but couldn’t reach anyone or leave a message in the full voicemail box. I tried emailing, but no response. So basically, I’ve been cheated by these guys. Not ordering from them ever again.

It's nothing to write to your friends about... It's a decent lunchtime BBQ spot I guess... The only thing I advise is that if you skipped that place for lunch, skip it for dinner too... The waffle fries were stale and the Mac n Cheese  barely had flavor... Thankfully the pulled pork was decent. Overall there is wayyyy better for way less... Give your business to someone that cares especially during these times!

I was excited to try this place out but the food was so dry and there was no sauce given and there was zero flavor to the food.... This is the worst I've eaten from anywhere 😭 I'm sorry to leave a bad review but stay away prob cause who ever is working today just didn't care and there was nothing good about the service and food 🤮
Always one of longtime favorite BBQ places

As soon as I walked in for pick up I knew I had made a good pick.  The food tastes as good as the restaurant smells. The barbeque sauce is everything. The buffalo wings are also perfectly seasoned. Some of the best bbq I've had in Brooklyn. Hands down
Love the food , but you can order the same thing but never get what you gotten before
One of the best BBQ spots in NY. Offers classic and unique dishes like the Char Siu pork, that is absolutely my favorite. Great selection of drinks and beers. Highly recommend.

This restaurant is absolutely one of the most attractive restaurants in the area. Whenever I come to this place I am awfully satisfied. They manage their very high  standard service and the topmost level of food  they serve. You definitely will enjoy this this place. Very  recommended.

I like to go with friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I visit this place often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The meals are fantastic and the crew is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we go to this place we enjoy a lovely time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.

We arrived at this place for lunch. my friend recommended this place.  Well, we were not disappointed. The staff members welcomed us with a smile and we felt fantastic. The meal was great. We had a great time and we shall absolutely come back again. Highly recommended.
Smoke is not a seasoning. Unbelievably small portions. no flavor. Horrible. So expensive. Never ever again.

I work in customer service.  When you serve the public invariably mistakes will happen.  The type of mistake not withstanding, most errors can be recovered by taking ownership and providing a fair solution to the problem.  On Saturday evening I stopped in to pick up some delicious burnt ends.  I don't live in Brooklyn, I live in queens but my friend put me on to them and I've been hooked since. When I got all the way home to queens some 40 minutes away.  I realized they had given me half of what I ordered.  I called to make them aware and without hesitation they offered a refund, or I could come back and get the proper order.  I told  them I would come by to pick up my order the following day.  When I went back the following day I explained the situation and they quickly gave me what I ordered and some extra for the trouble.  AND they apologized, SINCERELY.  I would have been satisfied with just what I paid for and the sincere apology that I received. The extra food ensured I'd not only be back, but it inspired me to write this review praising how well they recovered from a mistake.   Bottom line, the barbecue is here is delicious and if you live in Brooklyn what's your excuse I go there from Ozone Park queens!
Bbq sauce is great and the lunch specials are amazing! Waffles fries are yummmmm
This spot is worth a try. They serve big portions for reasonable prices. Consistently well organized and with awesome character. Highly recommended.
This place is worth trying. They serve big portions for affordable prices. Constantly well kept and with great atmosphere. Highly recommended.

It was ok but kind of turned off by the lack of customer service. Went here a few hours ago and it wasn't a great experience like my first visit. Went with a friend and we were not acknowledged when we came in. The person I was with had to ask if someone going to help us or do we need to use an app to order. Both gentlemen behind the counter acted like they were so busy, then one handed off the responsibility of taking our order to the one trying to prep food which to me seemed like he just didn't want to be bothered. Anyway we got rung up, my friend tried to make small talk but the guy at the register didn't respond. He took our order and said someone would call us. We had to wait outside and it was really cold which I didn't like because we are allowed to dine in but I guess they aren't comfortable with that yet despite being legally able to since the 30th. We waited a bit past 35 min, then got tired of freezing and went to check on our order as our food came out. Maybe when they allow people to dine in I'll try them again but takeout leaves a lot to be desired therefore I can't see myself goin back too soon. Mac and cheese with the meat as well as the cornbread was very good, regular mac was ok. Ribs seemed medium rare which I hated. Pulled pork was ok. $30 for 3 drinks which was alcohol esq...like the food - everything was neutral like not bad but not great either. Sucks we spent 80 on eehh food & drinks.

Solid local bbq joint in Brooklyn. Definitely go for the fattier cuts off bbq, and don't skimp on the use of their bbq sauce. Also definitely get a cup (or two!) Of their banana pudding, it is not to be skipped.  Coleslaw was a little disappointing as a side dish, better as a sandwich topping. Pricing is def a little expensive, but good bbq in NY is not cheap.

I would order from here again. The portion sizes are small tho, given the high price. Dessert first! Banana pudding. I think 6oz. The chess Cookie was a fabulous idea! There were a few slices of banana, and homemade flavored whipped cream. No pudding or custard. It was good, worth trying for sure. Pro tip: Make pudding with bourbon. The pickle chips were half sour, a little sweet, not very crisp; homemade tasting tho. A great compliment to the fat. Chilli Mac and cheese: YES! Chilli pepper spiced brisket cubes on top of Mac and cheese. The cheese sauce was homemade and not just Velveeta! It had a great flavor. Long live the cheese! Spare rib tips: With all BBQ, sometimes you get dry pieces. There were a mixture. I want to try the char siu next time. Two containers of BBQ sauce: Something appropriately sized. And this stuff was great. Tangy, hint of sweetness. Great flavor.

My boyfriend and I would eat here once a month. It tends to be pretty decent and it’s not too expensive. The odd time it has just be ok, subpar for them. But when we ordered it yesterday everything was cold and the meat was clearly so old it that it became tough to chew. And we requested extra sauce but received nothing.  I dmed them on Instagram to request store credit as I wanted to continue supporting them, instead of requesting a refund. However, they not only ignored my dm but then I also commented on their post to ask that they reply to me in case they hadn’t seen it and they deleted that.  Terrible customer service.
Great food, super nice employees, constantly good ambience. They charge affordable pricing and the food quality is excellent. I recommend this place.

The meat was really dry, everyone around the table is pretty much over the food at this point. The environment is super cozy and sweet. The staff nice and friendly.

The place is cozy, the staff is really nice, and the liquor pours are generous...but...the food was terrible. Thank goodness we chose to share a tray instead of ordering our own feasts (this was primarily because we were going to a comedy show afterwards and couldn't bring leftovers with us) as it would have been extra wasteful on our parts. The mac n cheese was hard and tasteless. The beans were so tart, I couldn't stomach more than 1 bite. The chopped chicken was dry and so was the brisket. Man, I love brisket so much and always look forward to when I can get some..but this one hurt my feelings lol. Awful food. Maybe I lived in the south too long and just have higher expectations? Maybe they just had a really bad night? I don't know, but I do know I'll never go back. Waste of money. 👎

I made a reservation for a group of 7 this past weekend and we all had a terrific time. The service was great by our waiter Kerril (spelling might be off), and the food was outstanding.  Waffle fries, wings, brisket, pulled pork, cheeseburger, collard greens, mac, and a few others I'm forgetting...we ate it ALL and it was ALL amazing.

I went there for take-out lunch today. I ordered the Beef Brisket sandwich $16.95 I got the waffle fries with it. The beef brisket sandwich came on a soft potato roll. The sandwich and fries were 5 Stars. They could have given more sliced pickles to put on the sandwich. It was very filling and tasty lunch.
I can't stop going back if I tried

Visited Fletchers only because we won a $50 gift certificate at a fund raiser. In short we have never experienced worse BBQ. Brisket so dry and overcooked it was hard to chew and swallow. We threw it out. Burnt ends were nothing but chunks of flabby fat. Pulled pork - the meat was overcooked to the point of texturelessness and mixed with sweet ketchupy gloop to compensate. The ribs were sadly as dry as the brisket. I love barbecue, and spend large amounts of my summer making it in the back yard. Fletchers was a massive disappointment.

The baked beans were amazing with pieces of meat, but the Mac and cheese left us wishing it was a bit better in flavor. Had a very nice time with a nice atmosphere on a weekday accompanied with good music and games on the TVs.

I did not taste the meat The corn bread I would rate a 2. The coleslaw 2. Completely tasteless but sometimes that's okay. The waffle fries a 2. I understand the "bbq flavor" I just don't want to taste sugar on my fries. The staff was kind but tired.

The brisket ends are perfection. The brisket fries are spectacular. It’s not cheap but it is delicious. However, the service is just miserable. Hire happier people. The Gowanus location is a bit dark and the staff seems unhappy but again, the brisket is amazing.

Perfectly good barbecue place, prices are a bit out of whack ($29/lb for brisket in Gowanus?) but overall the quality is there. Wait service at the tables, and there's a bar-like area as well. Order by the "serving" or fraction of a pound, but be sure the order is repeated back correctly lest you receive something you didn't know you wanted (though the unexpected rib tips were tasty).  Ordering moist (fatty) brisket has been a bit unreliable; on a recent visit it came virtually lean, which was dry and not the greasy, fatty spectacle I have enjoyed in the past. The rib tips were a good value (though I wanted burnt ends), and everything had a heavy smokiness that made the meal better. Greens (vegetarian) continued in that smoky vein. Waffle fries dusted with dry rub excelled, to my surprise.  The barbecue sauce wasn't needed but sure, let's add that to the fries. And the sweet tea would make a Southerner proud. Overall, a solid pre-show stop and that will continue.

Got my order to go, but,next time I'll eat in.  Picnic table style and exceptional Bourbon selection.  Cornbread was delicious and nice size. I'll be back 👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾😋

Came in with high hopes and a foodie recommended. Had the Burnt Ends platter which wow’ed in the wrong direction. Bone dry chopped brisket, burnt end had the thickest inch long soft fat layer I’ve ever experienced. The bark seemed interesting, yet I had to saw it off and slice the inch of fat, then reattach to the remaining meat. Fries blah and was assured the cornbread would be in the side and didn’t realize it’s directly touching both meat sections — and speaking of careless placement; ketchup packets were on top of the raw pickles and peppers ( commercial mass produced wrapping touching pickled veggies = tainted & inedible ) . Oh, and that was $30. My wife liked the collard greens, yet I couldn’t discern any unique flavor or ingredients. Hoping they just had an off night.

Adequate Food with NYC Price Tag  As you often find at Barbecue, there’s less than a dozen items in building (a plus) but somehow the staff knows too little about any of them (huge minus).  Feels like this menu relies too much on sugar.  Pit beans have a nice smoke.  For me, if youre going to smoke an entire brisket, you may as well offer sliced fatty brisket not just chopped lean mean in sauce with craisins. Collards tasty but did need so much celery.  I find that the lax’d picnic table ambience has ruined server’s perceived responsibilities across the board in BBQ places. Please know the menu, check on customers and be knowledgeable and aware. Or make me order at the counter.  Not a demotion but just a fun story, I was offered the special of the day Rib Tips and a Beer for $13, and I said oh thanks I don’t drink. Server responded, why would that matter (confused). I said oh because half of that special is booze 🙃.

Overpriced. Good quality meats though, but you are nickle and dimed. An iced tea is 3$ and there are no free refills. The ordering process is also slow and confusing.

Honestly, the best bbq in the neighborhood.  Big tables too.  Bring some people, have some brisket, maybe a beer, hang out.

Very disappointed ... went there last weekend.  The food was inferior as far as I was concerned.  The ribs my son got were COLD and RARE...the BBQ chicken I had was COLD AND DRY..my husband's chicken sandwich consisted of chopped up chicken on a bun...nothing special.  The collard greens were 'okay,' but cold, as was the Mac and Cheese sides, and the corn bread also dry and not what corn bread should be. Alright BBQ. Not the best I've tried but nice and cozy.

Anybody that knows me already know my undying love for BBQ. It doesn't take much for me to devour my food. With that being said, I really enjoyed the ribs and the pork. Some of the burnt-ends and hot links I've had.  The place is nothing flashy but it does carry craft beers.

I grew up in South Carolina and worked at a foodiot-worthy sandwich joint myself. I always made a point of trying BBQ along any country road I found myself. I've only been to Fletchers twice but I'm making a point to return. The pulled pork sandwich was rich in flavor, almost falling off the fluffy potato roll, and required no added sauce. The pulled rib sandwich was as delicious as it was messy. Some may be turned off by the bare-bones presentation, self-service and the messy way the meat falls off the bun, but it's a nod to some true whole-hog bbq I've had served on paper plates in Hemingway, South Carolina. That being said, in my opinion this presentation and service seemed contrived when I was the only one in the restaurant at the time. You could bring me my food and ring me up later. It may seem trivial but the stools were a tad bit low for the beautiful wooden tables, and I'm 6 feet tall. The restaurant itself needs some breaking in. I can't put a finger on it, but without a lively eat-in crowd, I felt rather awkward eating there. My suggestion would be to hold events, BBQ sampler parties, or altogether advertise the space more. The staff seemed genuinely interested in the craft of BBQ and Fletcher the owner seems sincere about what he's doing. No doubt, I'll be coming back. Help me break this place in, so the vibe matches the soulful food.
This is the best bbq joint in Brooklyn. Better than dino bbq. Better than hometown. This is where i discovered good bbq. I love the corn bread
Brisket was tender and tasty the cornbread supreme!!!!!
Great place!

Growing up in GA and living all over the south I've had some of the best and worst BBQ in the world, fletchers is definitely one of the worst. Starting with the sandwich they didn't properly cook it and found chunks of raw pork mixed in with the cooked ones, on top of that the service was less then exceptional. All and all, if you want decent BBQ I'd recommend pork slope on 5th ave.

Just finished eating here and the food is to die for! Amazing ribs, chicken and sausage all pit smoked to perfection! The beans are amazing as well, as they have a nice home made flavor. I'll definitely be making a return here! I'm totally stuffed from the generous portion they served me! Definitely recommend this place! Yum!!

Always like exploring this usual industrial commercial area of Brooklyn. You find quite a few gems of a restaurant. This time it's a wonderful BBQ joint. You smell the smoked fired up wood all over the block. Picked up a full rack of ribs with some bbq chicken. The rack of ribs was tender and juicy with a nice smoke flavor. The chicken also had a nice flavorful seasoning and was tender as well. The bbq sauce that accompanied had a nice spicey kick which matched up well with the ribs. Pick up a order and settle in on the picnic style tables to gobble up some ribs.
Ok not what I expected be honest I thought they appear a bit unsanitary too much smoked in the BBQ gave us stomach pains My friend got upset stomach
awesome place clean+polite+great taste= happy costumer.... ribs on point best smoked ribs in Brooklyn
all I can say is WOW .... Amazing !!!! a must try and repeat
Some of the best brisket I've had. you probably need not look further if your got that craving for some real good Q. I'll be back next time im in town for sure.

Ahmazing! No spot in Manhattan comes even close to the taste that Fletcher's meat packs. I don't know how they do it but it tastes so awesome. Try the ribs/pork belly/rib tips and brisket even if you are not a fan of it.
Fantastic and authentic. These guys are for real, and great at what they do. Keep going!

This is the perfect place for a post-concert meal.  I had the opportunity to take two friends of mine to this delicious place. This is what we ordered:  Pulled pork 1/4 chicken 1/2 rack of ribs Mac & Cheese Baked beans Baked potato salad corn bread  It was a delicious and filling meal. The mac & cheese could have been a lot better, but the pulled pork, smothered in their delicious bbq sauce, oh my, my, my, it was a feast for a king.  I'd recommend you try this place out if you're in the area. Good choice for those looking for some delicious BBQ.
I've been looking for high quality barbecue since moving here in late June. Fletcher's delivers on that, and then some. Loved the laid back atmosphere and the friendly employees. Found my go-to spot!

This has to be some of the best BBQ I have ever had. I have been all around NY BBQ and to TX (Salt Lick and Two Brothers), FL, SC, NC, VA,WV, MT, WA and OR and have sampled BBQ in all of them. Fletcher's really has it down. All of the meats are hot, tender juicy and well seasoned. So many of these places over season their food and make it way too salty (many times its also dried out). These guys have a very good range on all of their meats, including the sides which are really well done. Worth the trip to Brooklyn and with so many places for dessert locally, its a destination!
(Translated by Google) Eat very nice with very kind people  (Original) Menjar boníssim amb gent molt amable
Amazing

The staff here is always friendly and welcoming. Good is fast. Every dish here is delicious and flavorful! Not sure what the complaints are about Prices, smokiness and fat....you can eat lunch here for about 15 bucks, BBQ meat IS smoked and burnt ends ARE the fatty part of the cut. It's ALL right on to me!

I loved this place... nice and cozy and super friendly ! The burnt ends are amazing! We have almost tried everything there and keep going back to those burnt ends.Love the beans and fridge pickles. Matt is very gracious and a self taught bbqer, I think he is on the right path! The tri tip is good at a med rare ...but the ribs are great ! Next time I'm trying the duck ! It is expensive....but I get my brisket fix and thats worth it !!

This is probably the most awesome accidental find in NYC so far.  I stopped by here with a friend to grab a bite to eat and was pleasantly surprised. It was one of those moments where you want to try everything on the menu could only choose a few. I gravitated towards the brisket and lamb ribs were a special so we definitely had to try those. We also ordered bbq'd duck wings and some collard greens as a veggie. Pretty much everything but the duck wings were phenomena, I wasn't too crazy about the wings.  Anyway, if you're ever in the Brooklyn area, give this place a try. You won't be disappointed.

My friend and I were early for a Google event so we decided to check this place out last week.  We were hungry but didn't want to spoil our appetite so we didn't want to order too much.  We shared the lamb ribs (3 bones), Burnt ends, the duck wings (3 drums), and a medium collar greens. The lamb ribs and burnt ends were too fatty but very juicy (makes sense). And the duck wings were chewy and dry but had a great smokey flavor. We admired the exotic cuts of meats. We could have been safe by ordering the brisket but we didn't. I liked the cafeteria style and they had cool drink. The collar greens did help cut the greasiness and served as a good palate cleanser. A cocktail would have been better but we had somewhere else to go. I liked that the bathroom had hot water and paper towels to help wash of my hands. I despise places with no hot water!  It's unfortunate that I do not venture to this part of town but i'm glad picked this place to wet my appetite. I do wish bbq places give corn bread with every entree like in Jersey but I understand peeps gotta make $.

Went a little out of the way to try this place, heard it was very good. The meat was definitely well made, though the brisket did have a little too much fat on it for my taste. Sauce was pretty good, though they only had one bottle(would love to have 3 or 4 choices), but definitely a go to place if you are in the area.

You must order the burnt brisket ends. They're pretty fatty but even eating around it, you'll have a solid meal. The pulled pork is also good on its own but next time I would order the full sandwich. The cornbread was also great, obviously homemade and heavy.  It has a cafeteria feel and a popular spot for families, so be warned. Solid beer offerings and very friendly and helpful staff.  I've been to their popup shop and thought the brisket sandwich was fantastic, so eat that!

I wish Fletcher's was better I really do. It looks good, it smells good but it just doesn't deliver. Overall the meat had decent flavor it just wasn't moist enough. It wasn't something that could be fixed with BBQ sauce that sits in squeeze bottles on the tables. Even the Mac and Cheese and coleslaw just seemed kind of dry. Cornbread too. It's so close to being good it's really a shame. Oh and it's not cheap.

Heard some interesting things so decided to check it out. I now feel stuffed but satisfied. Had some pulled pork, burnt ends (fatty and flavorful), cornbread and overly cheesy (but a good thing) mac and cheese. Was also going to get the duck they had on special because it looked so good but filled up quickly. Very small bar and small selection on beers on tap although I enjoyed my Brooklyn IPA anyway but huge selection of bourbon and whiskey. Very friendly staff who walked me away from the bar and showed me and explained all the meats they had to offer. Very knowledgeable and friendly and I could tell he had a passion for what he was doing. Looking for a smokehouse I'd recommend giving this place a chance.

Price uber high portions small.  The lemonade didn't even have a pow lemony taste to it. I had brisket that had no flavor but smokey. Mac and cheese needs some soul. I know there is better barbecue in NYC. No more thank you!

Fletcher's serves barbecue sandwiches for carnivores. I don't think they have much for vegetarians beyond a bag of chips. I realize that barbecue is largely focused on meat but not having a vege option is poor form. Brisket is excellent, and by far the best thing they make. Pork is ok, nothing special. Ditto goes for the chips, which fail to hit the spot. There aren't many tables in Pier 57, and the few that were there were occupied, despite the hour, inclement weather, and recent opening. I imagine seating will become scarcer still as time goes by. Swing by for a brisket sandwich and pleasant service, and enjoy the funky, arty space that is Pier 57.
Passable food, but extremely overpriced. Should have cost half as much. Don't think I'll ever even consider another visit.

place seems to be pretty popular with the locals, communal style table seating, itsy bitsy bar, mixed cocktails on the weaker side but tasty, three beers on draft, bottled selection reasonable (you will not find your regular bud/amstel/heinken style of labels however). very attentive and pleasant staff, coriander pork was good, but not sensational, the group of fiends i was there with seemed to enjoy their food pretty much though, i do have to agree about the prices with the rest of reviewers. over all we had a good experience, might drop by again if in the area but won't be making a special trip.

This is top tier barbecue, but it's crazy expensive, and it's not the best barbecue in the city. The only way they could justify these prices is if it was just completely out of this world. It's good, but for less money, Dinosaur and Fette Sau are both better and cheaper. I've also found that it can be uneven. One time the food was pretty dry and bland. Two other times it was delicious.

You can tell the care in which it is cooked. they review before you purchase the staff was very nice. And it may cost more than a dallas bbq's but to me for the atmosphere and food it was worth it. The beans are extremely good and the sauce was also good.

Food was good, but the price for the product was a little steep.  I get their mission, but with the bbq in the area and that will open (i.e. Fort Reno, Dino BBQ), it's going to be a BBQ throwdown in Gowanus soon and Fletcher's, while tasty, won't be my go to.  I love family style seating, I love Hoisin Duck, but I can get half of that duck for $7 in Chinatown and I would be as happy.  I'd go again, but probably not my first choice.

BBQ sauce was phenomenal! Smoked turkey very good, wish the ribs were a bit more done. And the brisket was tasty but also wish it was a tad more done. Rolls very small, but good. Mac n Cheese to die for! Loved the wooden tables and experience and feel of the place. Will def go again if in the area.
Great BBQ

The food was waaaaaay too overpriced for the quality & quantity I received. It tasted fine but it wasn't the bestest BBQ I've tasted and for those prices, I expected near perfection. Nice staff though.
